Argentinian choripan

taste.com.au480min15min95min

These deluxe Argentinian hot dogs are made even better with the bright flavours of the chimichurri sauce, which is spicy and fresh.

  • 2 ripe tomatoes
  • 75 g red bell pepper deseeded, finely chopped
  • 75 g red onion finely chopped
  • 30 g extra virgin olive oil
  • 15 g red wine vinegar
  • 6 Smoky Chorizo Sausages
  • 4 long crusty rolls or baguettes

Chimichurri sauce

  • 20 g fresh parsley
  • 2 garlic cloves crushed
  • 1 g dried oregano leaves
  • 0.5 g chilli flakes
  • 30 g extra virgin olive oil
  • 30 g red wine vinegar
  1. Use a small sharp knife to cut the tomatoes into quarters. Use a teaspoon to remove the seeds and discard. Finely chop the flesh and place in a large bowl.
  2. Add the capsicum, onion, oil and vinegar to the bowl with the tomato and season well. Stir to combine and set aside to develop the flavours.
  3. For the chimichurri sauce, place all of the ingredients in a bowl and mix until well combined. Season. Set aside for 1 hour to develop the flavours.
  4. Meanwhile, preheat a chargrill pan or barbecue grill plate on medium heat. Cook chorizo, turning often, for 10 minutes or until charred and just cooked through.
  5. Transfer chorizo to a chopping board and cut in half lengthways. Cook, cut side down, for 2-3 minutes or until slightly charred. Transfer to a plate. Cover with foil.
  6. Cut rolls lengthways, until almost cut through. Open and grill, cut side down, for 2 minutes. Divide chorizo among rolls, top with chimichurri and tomato mixture.
